		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Serpent betrays SWCCG   Vancouver, BC<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.94)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=2021'>Alan "Serpent" Sagan</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=2021&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> February 10, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Yes it&#39;s true... lord of the rings has sucked me in.  What does a game need focloberrson to play it?  Fun?  Well.. not really, it needs fun people.. and lord of the rings has fun people.  Support?  yes, it has that..  and a used pile?  Nope, no used pile... well, 2/3 works well enough for me.  <br />
<br />
So I converted.  <br />
<br />
No!  Say it isn&#39;t so!  Say you&#39;ll always stay with Star Wars!<br />
<br />
As long as that $10,000 promise of decipher stays true, yes :P<br />
<br />
But I need something to stop me from drinking and smoking.. and card games are usually the best thing for that.<br />
<br />
So I caved a week ago, bought two boxes, went to my second tourny, and got 4th or 5th out of 20.  not bad,... I only lost to quite good decks.  I learned you have to account for a rampaging cage troll :)<br />
<br />
I spent a little bit of time thinking this week while doing all the engineering activities and classes around here.. which isn&#39;t easy; it being E-week here (the week the VW bugs are always hung.. no, we didn&#39;t hang one of the golden gate this year.. only a bridge in town), plus eight third year courses are not conducive to playing cards..<br />
<br />
Let me give you an example of some of the events.<br />
<br />
Couch Potato races.  <br />
<br />
Four Geers sit on a couch, each with a pint in one hand, popcorn in the other.  The gun is shot, and the relay is on!  Geer number one downs the popcorn, slams the pint, runs for a TV, switches the channel, and boots it back to the couch... upon which geer number two downs the popcorn, slams the pint...  and the total time is the time of the team.  <br />
It gets pretty good by the time a team has raced 3 times... the winners had a 50 second time, pretty decent.<br />
<br />
Well enough of that, this is a tournement report!<br />
<br />
I built two decks, a variation of Tennet&#39;s Don&#39;t Pee in the Twilight pool (I&#39;d accidently seen the deck over christmas... a friend of mine just forgot to put other companions in his deck, even though it wasn&#39;t geared to be a choke deck, it worked quite well) and a mega dwarf delving deck.  I wasn&#39;t confident in the dwarf deck, since I hadn&#39;t seen it played before, and since it hasn&#39;t seen much popularilty on decktech... so i went with the choke.<br />
<br />
<br />
Game 1: Alan Sagan vs Gabriel<br />
Well gosh darnit, I play him every tournement.. aww well.  Turns out we&#39;re both playing moria... and I can&#39;t quite remember what he started, I think it was gandalf.  so my deck is disadvantaged (moria is very good vs choke).  He goes, gives me some twilight, and I bring some cronies down, nothing spectacular.  My turn was great though... Saga of Elendil, Armor, Ranger&#39;s Sword, Hobbit Sword, Aragorn&#39;s Bow, Armor, No stranger to Shadow&#39;s.  My aragorn is set!  I move my one site, beat up an orc, and let him go.  He moves to site 4, upon which I promptly drop enough guys to overwhelm two companions, pippin and aragorn I believe.  I move my one site, letting him do almost nothing.. still roaming.  He moves to the bridge, where I now kill off Gandalf, leaving just frodo staring at me in the face... Victory is nigh.  I move, kill some with bow and/or aragorn, intuition another fight.  His turn, he drops 3 new companions, being crappy legolas, boromir, and one other guy... gosh darnit, how many companions is he playing!  I empty my hand by using They Are Coming, and manage to kill off everyone but frodo AGAIN.  I move to the bridge, but he doesn&#39;t have the armories out to swarm me properly, so no worries.  On his turn, he puts out another companion, but it isn&#39;t enough.  Frodo bites the big one.<br />
<br />
FW +3<br />
<br />
Game 2: Alan Sagan vs Shawn Van Dorn<br />
Quickest game of my life.  He starts Arwen and Legolas.. rangers and archery... Prancing Pony, Aragorn, give me lots of pool.  Oh, he also bid 5 burdens to go first.  Well, Enquea and a orc pop out, exert 3 times to kill the legomania... oops!  I don&#39;t like point ears.  the Orc dies, and aragorn gets pumped to kill Enquea, and he hops to site 3.  My turn, i drop a No stranger, a bounder, move.  He can&#39;t do jack :P  <br />
His turn:  he drops boromir and some otehr things, giving me tons of twilight.., moves to site 4, where i drop two runners, a scout, and a guard commander, and a scimitar on a runner.  Well, the runner goes up vs frodo... two pumps from the commander = power 9 runner = dead frodo.  Game.<br />
<br />
FW +3<br />
<br />
hmm.. I felt bad.  It was neat, but that&#39;s the problem with this game... a bad draw, or a good draw, can equal early death.  I hope he doesn&#39;t quit, I think this was his first tournement.<br />
<br />
Game3: Vs Sean M<br />
Well gosh darnit, this is the Cave Troll and Gandalf man.  He plays the standard super big cavetroll deck.. lots of runners, armories, key wardens just to get a troll+hammer out, then uses Gandalf plus aragorn, legolas to shoot tons.  <br />
He starts Legolas and Sam, and bids high, using same to get rid of the burdens... he started that dumb hobbit site i think, didn&#39;t help either of us.  He double hops, I drop nobody, and he complains about the worst hand ever.<br />
I drop a No stranger, move, and he compalins about not being able to play anything :P<br />
He moves a site without deploying anything, now he&#39;s at site 4... swarms and they are coming pop out, and I use They Are Coming to empty my hand, and draw up more by getting scavengers/scimitars.  Same Bites it, Swarms gets stacked on.<br />
I drop some possessions, using the Forest Site 2 text to draw new cards, and move to site3.  He puts out almost nothing, I kill them/stealth them, and end my turn.<br />
His turn, he moves to the bridge.  With Legolas and Frodo.  Goodbye, mr elf!  Swarms + they are coming kills the elf, while a power according to his stature is granted to frodo, saving him.  But he&#39;s all alone!  Sean talks about how hard it is to find 3 gandalfs, 2 wizards are never late, and 3 aragorns in a 60 card deck :P<br />
On my turn, I play a bounder and a thrarin, move, removing two using council courtyard, and give him four to play with.  Not enough to swarm me effectively, although Thrarin bit the dust.  <br />
He doesn&#39;t play anyone, moves to site 6, and swarms of goblins kill Mr. Frodo.  Game!<br />
<br />
FW +3<br />
<br />
Let it be known that a bad draw sucks.  Let it be known that a choke deck makes a bad draw suck even more!  <br />
Sean and I had a rematch, and he found aragorn and gandalf very early... Gandalf combined with two archers = swarms don&#39;t work.  He races ahead very early, and my shadow can&#39;t touch him, and my fellowship can&#39;t keep up.  So if it wasn&#39;t bad luck, he would&#39;ve won.<br />
<br />
Game 4: David Houle<br />
Dave has also betrayed Star Wars.  He was one of the better players around here, always giving me a run for my money, though rarely beating me :)<br />
Will this tradition continue?<br />
He starts hobbit friendly boromir and merry, and the prancing pony.  He drops a sword right away for merry and boromir, and moves.  I drop enough guys to.. do almost nothing.  He moves again.  I again drop guys to... get beaten to a pulp.  woopee.<br />
But my hand is set for my turn... I drop a bounder and a saga of elendil, plus a no shadows, and move.  He drops a swarms, an armory, and i think a runner.  the runner DIES. :)<br />
he moves to site 4, whereupon the large shadow, the findings of they are coming... don&#39;t help me.  I only drop four guys, and he has four guys out... so all my guys die.  yay.  I draw up, and he ends his turn. <br />
I drop an armor, rangers sword, hobbit sword at site 2 and get to draw some cards for it... and move.. he&#39;s able to drop 3 goblin runners, each with scimitars and armory out.  gosh darnit, that&#39;s really not helping me clog up his hand.  Aragorn is a mighty defender, taking two on at once, and frodo takes a wound... so 3 runners go on swarms.  ouch.<br />
his turn, he moves to site five, whereupon i lay the smack down.  I get something like 7 or 8 guys out.. two scavengers go on aragorn, a few guys on frodo, merry, and just one on boromir (in hindsight, i should&#39;ve added more on boromir, to force him to exert to kill them, instead of being able to beef up hobbits).  Aragorn bites it, being a wuss, and some wounds are felt by all, while many cards get stacked on my swarms.<br />
I move to site 4... and see almost no guys come at me.  Yawn.<br />
He moves to site 6, and the combination of swarms, my hand, they are coming = a dead boromir... leaving merry and frodo staring me down.  I feel the end is nigh..<br />
I move to site 5... and 5 goblins come to fight.. along with a cave troll.. vs aragorn and frodo..  he had three armories out.  <br />
Could this be game?<br />
Could I be giving up a tourney win to Dave?<br />
NO!<br />
Aragorn is the man, with his 5 vitality due to a saga.  Instead of using it on archery, which isn&#39;t guaranteed with the armories out... I use it on defender +1.<br />
four times.<br />
Yes, aragorn took on 4 orcs and a cave troll.<br />
<br />
He didn&#39;t live to tell about it :P<br />
To prevent having them stacked on swarms, during the skirmish i sacked the saga to give him +2 strength, instantly killing him.  <br />
and a single orc couldn&#39;t kill frodo... neither couuld a cave troll, he couldn&#39;t find the sneaky little bugger :)<br />
so dave gets to go, and he can&#39;t put anyone out, and he forgets to transfer the sword to frodo.. and 4 orcs + a cave troll at site 6 ( a troll at six! ) means a dead frodo.  <br />
<br />
FW +3<br />
<br />
and I win the tournement.. hopefully I can only match the record i got for the local scene of SW around here...<br />
<br />
<br />
